<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4768.3.6>
    bibo:endPage "404" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2020-05-04" ;
    bibo:startPage "395" ;
    bibo:volume "4768" ;
    dc:creator "Rodriguez-Silva, Rodet; Torres-Pineda, Patricia; Josaphat, James" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Limia mandibularis, a new livebearing fish (Cyprinodontiformes: Poeciliidae) from Lake Miragoane, Haiti" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784086>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784088>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784090>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784092>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784094>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784096> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784086>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Limia mandibularis sp. nov., holotype OMNH 86828, adult male 35.5 mm SL (top) and paratype OMNH 86829, adult female 41.0 mm SL (bottom)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3784086/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784088>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Mouth of a cleared specimen of Limia mandibularis sp. nov. (OMNH 86831, female, 41.5 mm SL) showing the peculiar arrangement of bones of the upper and lower jaws. Premax: premaxillar, max: maxilla, dent: dentary, ang: anguloarticular, qu: quadrate" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3784088/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784090>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Head of Limia mandibularis sp. nov. showing the protuberance in the lower jaw (a), the single preorbital canal forming an open groove (b) and the single preopercular canal forming an open groove (c). Red lines show the quadrato-mandibular joint forming nearly a right angle between the front of the mouth and the inferior edge of the eye globe." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3784090/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784092>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Cleared and stained gonopodium tip of Limia mandibularis sp. nov., paratype OMNH 86831, adult male, 38.5 mm SL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3784092/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784094>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Female of Limia mandibularis sp. nov (48.5 mm SL) showing coloration in a live specimen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3784094/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784096>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Habitat where Limia mandibularis sp. nov. was collected. The locality is found at the north end of Lake Miragoane and corresponds with locality represented by the white circle in Figure 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3784096/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

